// tailwind-prose-coverage.scrml
// SPEC §26.6 end-to-end fixture for the prose utility family.
// Exercises: prose, prose-slate, prose-lg (composition), not-prose opt-out,
// plus diverse descendant elements (h1..h4, p, blockquote, code, pre, table,
// ul, ol, hr, img, a, kbd, figure, figcaption).

<article class="prose prose-slate prose-lg">
    <h1>Typography Plugin Test</h1>
    <p>This article exercises the <code>prose</code> utility family per SPEC §26.6. The container has <code>class="prose prose-slate prose-lg"</code> applied, so nested typography should pick up base styling, slate color overrides, and large-size scaling.</p>

    <h2>Headings</h2>
    <p>The <kbd>prose</kbd> family styles <code>h1</code> through <code>h4</code> with progressive sizes.</p>

    <h3>Inline content</h3>
    <p>Links like <a href="https://example.com">example.com</a> render with prose link styling. <strong>Bold text</strong> uses the heading color. Inline <code>code</code> appears in monospace with backtick markers.</p>

    <h4>Code blocks</h4>
    <pre><code>function greet(name) {
  return `Hello, ${name}`;
}</code></pre>

    <h2>Lists</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Unordered item one</li>
        <li>Unordered item two with <em>emphasis</em></li>
        <li>Unordered item three</li>
    </ul>

    <ol>
        <li>Ordered item one</li>
        <li>Ordered item two</li>
        <li>Ordered item three</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Blockquotes</h2>
    <blockquote>
        <p>A quoted passage uses italic styling, a left border in the variant's 200-shade, and the variant's 900-shade for body color.</p>
    </blockquote>

    <h2>Tables</h2>
    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Property</th>
                <th>Description</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>prose</td>
                <td>Base nested-typography styling</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>prose-slate</td>
                <td>Slate-tone color overrides</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>prose-lg</td>
                <td>Large size scaling</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <hr/>

    <h2>Opt-out (not-prose)</h2>
    <p>The block below is marked <code>not-prose</code> and should escape prose styling entirely:</p>

    <div class="not-prose">
        <h3>Plain heading inside not-prose</h3>
        <p>This paragraph uses default browser styling, not prose typography.</p>
        <a href="#">A link with no prose styling</a>
    </div>

    <h2>Figures</h2>
    <figure>
        <img src="/example.png" alt="example"/>
        <figcaption>A caption rendered in the prose figcaption style.</figcaption>
    </figure>
</article>
